Steps to Reproduce:
auto sprite = cocos2d::Sprite::create("SpriteSileName.png");
sprite->setColor(cocos2d::Color3B::WHITE);
sprite->runAction(cocos2d::TintTo::create(0.0f, cocos2d::Color3B::RED));

In example above sprite does not change it's color all. 

But this code works properly
auto sprite = cocos2d::Sprite::create("SpriteSileName.png");
sprite->setColor(cocos2d::Color3B::WHITE);
sprite->runAction(cocos2d::TintTo::create(**0.0001f**, cocos2d::Color3B::RED));

It's needed to add zero multiplying check. At first glance cocos2d::TintBy action has same problem.

